N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 10 ยง 11.152 - Supervisory level qualifications

State Regulations
A supervising public health educator must meet the qualifications for local public health educator and have two years of experience as a public health educator or have a master's degree in public health or health education from a regionally accredited or New York State registered college or university and one year experience as a public health educator.
